      • showAppointments

        public void showAppointments​(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> appointmentList)
        Populates the tableview with appointments. LAMBDA EXPRESSION: sets the start and end columns in the tableview to specified date time format - For every appointment in the start and end columns, I get the value of the current appointment start and end time and format them with the specified format and set them as string values. A lambda is justified because the setCellValueFactory uses a callback as a parameter and is simpler than writing another function.
        Parameters:
        appointmentList - list of appointments to show in tableview.

      • checkBusinessHours

        private boolean checkBusinessHours​(java.time.ZonedDateTime zStartDT,
                                   java.time.ZonedDateTime zEndDT)
        Checks to make sure the appointment day/time is during business hours (Weekdays from 8 AM to 10 PM EST)
        Parameters:
        zStartDT - ZonedDateTime format of start date & time of appointment.
        zEndDT - ZonedDateTime format of end date & time of appointment.
        Returns:
